Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.
result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Naomi R Wilkins

records.addlTxt: Defendant is in compliance with the terms of the DPA. Due to the defendants compliance with the terms of the agreement, court cancelled with midpoint review hearing. Court scheduled the final review hearing.

Defendant Naomi R Wilkins in court.  Attorney Allison Marie Ritter in court for Naomi R Wilkins.  Prosecuting attorney Sarah Dahdouh in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Case in court for Deferred Prosecution Agreement hearing. 
Court is in receipt of  the Deferred Prosecution Agreement; Plea Questionnaire, Addendum to Plea Questionnaire and Elements of the Offense.
State advised the Court they have complied with the Victims' Rights Law. 

The parties have agreed to a deferred judgment agreement. 
The defendant was advised of her constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, and entered a plea of GUILTY
Defendant  examined as to the plea.  The parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  
The Court found the defendant guilty but WITHHELD entry of Judgment of Conviction.  
The Court reviewed the Early Intervention Program Deferred Prosecution Agreement with the defendant.  
The court approved the Deferred Prosecution Agreement and ordered the proceedings suspended until Review Hearing.  
Parties informed this matter has been reassigned to Judge Stark, Br. 17. Review Hearing scheduled
Review hearing scheduled for November 8, 2022 at 03:30 pm.
Elements of the Offense/WIS JI - Criminal

Defendant Naomi R Wilkins in court with attorney Allison Marie Ritter.  Katrina Amy Voge appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Case inc ourt for status. Defense awaiting DPA offer and requests an adjournment. Case adjourned back to Br 30.  Deferred prosecution agreement hearing scheduled for August 25, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Naomi R Wilkins in court with attorney Amanda R. Kremer on behalf of Allison Kremer.  Adam Joseph Best appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Naomi R Wilkins appeared by video means with Attorney.  
Case in court for status conference.  Defense is requesting adjourned status date to determine case posture. Case adjourned to Branch 30. Status Conference is scheduled on June 29, 2022 at 1:30pm.

Defendant Naomi R Wilkins in court.  Adam Joseph Best appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Case in court for pretrial conference. Defendant appears without counsel. Indigency hearing proceeded.  Based upon the defendant's statements, the court found the defendant eligible for appointment of counsel at county expense.  The court appointed Attorney Allison Ritter to represent the defendant; counsel to be paid at the rate of $100.00 per hour. The court ordered the defendant to repay Milwaukee County for attorney fees at the rate of $25.00 per month beginning on 07-01-2022  and then the 1st of each month there after.  Failure to make timely payments according to the imposed payment schedule may result in a civil judgment, subject to tax intercept. Order Appointing Attorney at County Expense signed and filed. Case adjourned to Branch 30.  Status conference scheduled for May 19, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.

Defendant Naomi R Wilkins in court.  Mallory R Davis appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant is advised that this case is assigned to Judge Richards, Branch 30.  
Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause. Defendant received a copy of the complaint and was advised of right to counsel and maximum penalties. Court entered a plea of not guilty on behalf of the Defendant.  Court reserves Defendant's right to file a substitution of judge pursuant to Sec. 971.20 right to challenge probable cause and to have complaint read until Defendant's next scheduled court appearance. Defendant was given a referral to the Public Defender's Office. Defendant MAY be Public Defender eligible.  
The case is adjourned for a Pretrial Conference in Br. 30  Pre-trial conference scheduled for April 21, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Summons mailed.  Defendant ordered into room 221 Safety Building on 3/31/22 @ 2:30p
